reading this when I

00:04:10.580 --> 00:04:12.560
was nine years old for
the very first time,

00:04:12.560 --> 00:04:16.459
and thinking that this statement
was the most amazing quote I'd

00:04:16.459 --> 00:04:18.260
ever read in a book before.

00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:20.262
Because, first of all, I
had never heard someone

00:04:20.262 --> 00:04:22.220
say that you could just
determine that you were

00:04:22.220 --> 00:04:23.150
going to have an adventure.

00:04:23.150 --> 00:04:25.608
Like I'm going to arrange a
nice little adventure for seven

00:04:25.608 --> 00:04:27.400
and invite my friends.

00:04:27.400 --> 00:04:29.870
And that you could have
people come with you.

00:04:29.870 --> 00:04:32.150
And as I became an
educator, I thought, man,

00:04:32.150 --> 00:04:35.150
wouldn't it be great if
every day, instead of lesson

00:04:35.150 --> 00:04:37.760
